      "moreInfoUrl": "https://seamlesstaxation.com",
      "userJourney": "1. In the proof of concept, a seller issues an invoice. Before any money moves, the buyer's system performs an identity lookup on the seller's verifiable organisational credential, issued by Credenco. The check rejects shell companies before the payment can start.\r\n\r\n2. The buyer pays from an organisational wallet, at a point-of-sale terminal or online. The wallet holds the organisation's credentials, so every payment is bound to a verified legal identity.\r\n\r\n3. At the moment of payment the amount splits automatically: the net amount settles with the seller, the VAT portion transfers directly to the tax authority's wallet. No one has to set money aside or file anything.\r\n\r\n4. The payment carries a cryptographic reference to the underlying invoice. Invoice and payment are verifiably linked in a single audit trail that all parties can check without exposing the underlying business data to anyone else.\r\n\r\n5. The tax authority follows VAT flows in real-time through its portal and handles settlement and refunds over the same infrastructure. Discrepancies surface immediately instead of months after a quarterly declaration.\r\n\r\n6. The entrepreneur does nothing: no reserving, no calculating, no declaring. The invoice is the return.\r\n\r\nThe demonstration is a simplified consumer version of this business-to-business flow: at a physical point-of-sale setup, visitors buy a product, pay with a demonstration wallet, and see the VAT reach the tax authority's wallet on the spot.",
      "country": "NL"
    },
